    "comment": "Rationale: Application of noradrenaline to cultured hippocampal neurons induces a reduction in the frequency of miniature EPSCs (Fig 4). Application of the selective alpha1-agonist cirazoline also induced a reduction in the mEPSC frequency, but no change in mEPSC amplitude (Fig. 4d, f). These findings indicate that presynaptic G-Protein coupled Alpha1-adrenergic receptors modulate synaptic transmission upon activation.. Experimental description: For the preparation of hippocampal cultures, hippocampi were carefully dissected from E18 rat embryo brains",
